  "name": "Breaching the Gulf",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/spells/light-eerie-1.jpg",
  "sort": 0,
  "flags": {},
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 15th level, your <em>caster level</em> is increased by 3 when casting spells of the teleportation subschool. In addition, once per day you can <em>teleport</em> a single creature within 30 feet into the void of space if it fails a <em>Will</em> save. The save DC is equal to 10 + 1/2 your sorcerer level + your <em>Charisma</em> modifier. The target can attempt a new <em>saving throw</em> as a <em>full-round action</em> each round to return. While trapped in the airless void, the target suffers 6d6 points of cold damage per round and must hold its breath or begin to suffocate.</p>"
    },
